    public abstract class PluginFilterGeneric
extends ProcessImageGuiDisplayGeneric
implements GenericImageProcess
    Generic implementation of a plugin based on the notion of a Generic Image Process. This class implements the code ran by the plugin, executing the Generic Image Process on the current image retrieved by the framework. A method allows to test the plugin without deploying it on the platfrom, by loading

    • Method Detail

      • runOnCurrentImage

        public void runOnCurrentImage(java.lang.Object inputObject)
        Method that retrieves the input image, and possibly copies it to initialize the current image. Then calls method @link{GenericImageProcess#runProcess()} method, which is to be implemented in subclasses. If ProcessInputOutput.m_outputDataKind is equal to ProcessInputOutput.OutputDataKind.CreatedFromInputCopy, then the input image is duplicated
        Parameters:
        inputObject - The object to transmit to the process runProcess method

      • processOutput

        public void processOutput()
        Default output processing for the plugin. Assumes that the output object implements ImageCore. In case the output is not a single image, this method is to be overriden by a subclass class.

      • testPlugin

        public void testPlugin(java.lang.Object inputObject)
        Allows to test the plugin using an image file as input image. The RenderTool used to display the output is retrieved through Uses the internal attributes for the metadata title and the rendering tool for the output.
        Parameters:
        inputObject - The object to transmit to the process runProcess method GlobalOptions.getDefaultRenderTool()

        Parameters:
